                    </div>
                    <span>This, along with the book by Helen Gaines, is one of the best introductions to classical cryptology, but if you want to go further into contemporary cryptology, you'll need a more recent book. I like Applied Cryptology by Bruce Schneier.<P>For by far the best book on background but not for mathematics, try The Codebreakers by David Kahn. <P>All four belong on any crypto bookshelf.</span>
                  
